15 SECTION 1. BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF MARYLAND,
16 That the Laws of Maryland read as follows:
17 Article – Criminal Law
18 7–104.
19 (g) (2) Except as provided in paragraph (3) of this subsection, a person
20 convicted of theft of property or services with a value of at least $100 but less than $1,500,
21 is guilty of a misdemeanor and:
22 (i) is subject to:
